    <sect2 id="m4-working">
      <title>The m4 Macro Processor</title>

      <para>

        m4 is a macro processing language.  It does the seemingly
        un-interesting job of replacing macros with their definitions in
        the input, and copying it to the output.  This is what many
        <quote>pre-processors</quote> do.  It is used with several
        popular software pacakges like the sendmail program (where it is
        used to generate sendmail configuration files) and automake
        (where is it a pre-requisite for generating the configure
        scripts).  m4 has several uses, for instance, it can be used to
        update elements in the webpages of an entire website ensuring a
        standard look and feel.

      </para>

